  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> </font><b>Et O\n        ces ... </b><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p>V. Verlaine, <i>Parsifal</i>. [Eliot's note]\n        Verlaine's sonnet describes Parsifal, the questing\n        knight, resisting all sensual temptations to keep himself\n        pure for the Grail; Wagner's Parsifal had his feet washed\n        before entering the castle of the Grail.</p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td> </td>\n<td><a href=\"title_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Waste_A.htm\"><font>back to \"The Waste Land\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Et O ces ... V. Verlaine, Parsifal . [Eliot's note] Verlaine's sonnet describes Parsifal, the questing knight, resisting all sensual temptations to keep himself pure for the Grail; Wagner's Parsifal had his feet washed before entering the castle of the Grail. reference topics back to \"The Waste Land\"",
